Saturday, August 02, 2025


Lewes, DE is a coastal town in southern Delaware with a mild humid subtropical climate characterized by hot, humid summers and mild winters. It is located at the mouth of Delaware Bay, just inside of Cape Henlopen. The current NOAA weather station has been installed on a pier at the Cape May-Lewes Ferry Terminal since December 1990.
